annotationA: Anamorsin homolog; Component of the cytosolic iron-sulfur (Fe-S) protein assembly (CIA) machinery. Required for the maturation of extramitochondrial Fe-S proteins. Part of an electron transfer chain functioning in an early step of cytosolic Fe-S biogenesis. Electrons are transferred to the Fe-S cluster from NADPH via a FAD- and FMN-containing diflavin oxidoreductase. Has anti- apoptotic effects in the cell
annotationB: Uncharacterized protein; It is involved in the biological process described with: neuron projection morphogenesis; Belongs to the BolA/IbaG family
